WEBVTT

00:29.217 --> 00:30.302
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

00:33.388 --> 00:35.014
CHARACTERS, EVENTS, ORGANIZATIONS,
AND PLACES IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

00:35.015 --> 00:36.390
ALL CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
FILMED IN A SAFE ENVIRONMENT

00:36.391 --> 00:37.475
Huh?

00:37.476 --> 00:39.144
EPISODE 11

00:55.243 --> 00:58.080
THANKS FOR THE

01:16.264 --> 01:17.598
Kang Hyeokchan…

01:17.599 --> 01:19.768
KANG HYEOKCHAN
GLASS TUBE

01:20.560 --> 01:22.729
Why is this name here?

01:27.150 --> 01:29.235
Hospitalized? Hyeokchan?

01:29.236 --> 01:31.112
He hurt his hand badly in the lab.

01:31.113 --> 01:32.489
He even got surgery.

01:33.323 --> 01:36.201
How does he know Hyeokchan?

01:38.412 --> 01:40.080
OUTSIDE THE LAB

01:40.622 --> 01:42.165
"Lab"?

01:42.791 --> 01:44.041
NaClO.

01:44.042 --> 01:45.459
Sodium hypochlorite…

01:45.460 --> 01:47.128
I guess
you majored in that field.

01:47.129 --> 01:49.381
It seems like you majored
in engineering, not art.

01:53.093 --> 01:54.385
Huh?

01:54.386 --> 01:55.554
This is…

01:56.471 --> 01:59.723
I'm only visiting, so I'm not
authorized to treat patients directly.

01:59.724 --> 02:00.851
I came from Boston.

02:02.644 --> 02:03.645
Boston?

02:09.443 --> 02:11.235
There was
an international conference.

02:11.236 --> 02:12.571
Your school…

02:13.029 --> 02:16.783
- No, your former school…
-  That's enough.

02:22.205 --> 02:23.707
Boston Institute of Technology.

02:36.845 --> 02:37.846
Ah.

02:41.767 --> 02:42.768
Is she upstairs?

02:45.145 --> 02:46.730
THANKS FOR THE

03:13.131 --> 03:14.882
KANG HYEOKCHAN, GLASS TUBE, BLOOD

03:14.883 --> 03:17.344
KANG HYEOKCHAN HOSPITALIZED, WOMAN
THAT SOUND WAS HER BRACELET

03:27.521 --> 03:29.439
No…

03:39.324 --> 03:40.824
Let me tell you something cool.

03:40.825 --> 03:43.536
My dorm roommate is Korean,
and his name's Chan, too.

03:43.537 --> 03:45.704
You used to call him Chan.

03:45.705 --> 03:47.666
Your old boyfriend, Hyeokchan.

03:48.375 --> 03:49.501
Hyeokchan's roommate

03:50.502 --> 03:53.796
was Seonu Chan?

03:55.090 --> 03:56.591
SEONU CHAN

03:57.968 --> 03:59.051
Watch out!

03:59.052 --> 04:00.178
Song Haran!

04:01.179 --> 04:03.305
I met you for the first time
a few days ago.

04:03.306 --> 04:05.183
How long have you known me?

04:05.684 --> 04:08.143
Tell me how you know me.

04:08.144 --> 04:09.688
What are you hiding?

04:12.399 --> 04:13.608
He's known me

04:14.985 --> 04:16.194
for seven years.

04:39.759 --> 04:41.344
He knew my face

04:42.304 --> 04:44.180
and my name.

04:45.390 --> 04:46.599
It's nice to meet you.

04:46.600 --> 04:47.601
Ah…

04:48.435 --> 04:49.603
It's nice to meet you.

04:50.270 --> 04:53.565
I saw you up close earlier,
looking at the Sisley painting.

04:55.191 --> 04:56.359
No…

04:56.943 --> 04:58.612
This can't be right. No.

04:59.321 --> 05:00.404
No…

05:00.405 --> 05:01.989
Hey, it smells like rain.

05:01.990 --> 05:04.325
That's the smell
of organic matter diffusing.

05:04.326 --> 05:05.659
Petrichor.

05:05.660 --> 05:08.371
There's another guy
who speaks like him.

05:09.122 --> 05:10.789
She doesn't like eggplants.

05:10.790 --> 05:12.666
How do you know
I don't like eggplants?

05:12.667 --> 05:14.460
Yuck. The taste of neon alien.

05:14.461 --> 05:15.712
I'll eat those for you.

05:16.254 --> 05:17.339
The neon aliens.

05:18.965 --> 05:20.050
Then…

05:21.384 --> 05:22.636
all those messages…

05:24.054 --> 05:25.722
were him pretending to be Hyeokchan?

05:33.313 --> 05:34.314
No…

05:35.357 --> 05:37.316
That can't be. No.

05:37.317 --> 05:38.525
He'll explain everything.

05:38.526 --> 05:39.818
No…

05:39.819 --> 05:41.153
This doesn't make sense.

05:56.836 --> 05:58.462
Let's meet.

05:58.463 --> 05:59.713
Let's meet up and talk.

05:59.714 --> 06:01.091
I'll explain everything.

06:05.595 --> 06:06.930
No, please…

06:07.430 --> 06:08.431
Please.

06:09.015 --> 06:10.016
Please…

06:21.152 --> 06:23.780
It must have gotten mixed up
in my stuff back then.

06:24.572 --> 06:26.657
Just consider this pen

06:26.658 --> 06:27.701
a pen that I found for you.

06:30.453 --> 06:32.955
I think you owe me an explanation.

06:32.956 --> 06:34.582
I bought the same pen…

06:37.460 --> 06:38.920
when I was in the States.

06:39.921 --> 06:41.131
Then this pen…

06:42.674 --> 06:44.426
He knew everything…

07:13.246 --> 07:14.748
- Hey…
-  Don't come any closer.

07:23.882 --> 07:25.467
Boston Institute of Technology.

07:26.259 --> 07:27.677
Kang Hyeokchan's roommate.

07:28.720 --> 07:30.013
Have you really known me

07:31.181 --> 07:32.557
for seven years?

07:39.063 --> 07:40.732
- Song Haran.
- Don't say my name.

07:42.358 --> 07:43.443
Did you have fun

07:44.277 --> 07:45.986
pretending to be Kang Hyeokchan?

07:52.410 --> 07:53.787
Seonu Chan,

07:54.788 --> 07:55.872
who are you?

08:01.753 --> 08:03.295
The Seonu Chan

08:03.296 --> 08:06.089
I liked and trusted
until just a few hours ago…

08:06.090 --> 08:07.592
Who is he, really?

08:10.053 --> 08:11.678
Who are you?

08:15.141 --> 08:16.434
I'm sorry.

08:16.976 --> 08:19.312
I shouldn't have let you
find out like this.

08:19.854 --> 08:21.230
I should've told you…

08:21.231 --> 08:23.900
No wonder you were so flustered
in front of the doctor.

08:24.609 --> 08:26.319
You didn't want to get caught,

08:27.445 --> 08:29.864
because she knew you were in Boston.

08:30.782 --> 08:32.283
Because I couldn't find out.

08:32.992 --> 08:34.994
- I'll explain everything.
- Tell me.

08:36.287 --> 08:37.455
Did you message me

08:38.164 --> 08:40.250
seven years ago,
pretending to be Hyeokchan?

08:40.917 --> 08:42.085
Is that true?

08:46.089 --> 08:47.090
Answer me.

08:49.217 --> 08:52.887
Did you really deceive me
and pretend to be Hyeokchan

08:54.055 --> 08:55.223
behind his back?

08:59.853 --> 09:00.854
I'm sorry.

09:04.524 --> 09:05.525
Why?

09:07.527 --> 09:08.570
Why did you do that?

09:11.614 --> 09:12.615
Our laptops

09:13.700 --> 09:15.951
got switched once.

09:21.082 --> 09:23.168
Did you have fun
chatting with me like that?

09:24.085 --> 09:27.129
Did you build some kind of fantasy
and start liking me?

09:27.130 --> 09:29.507
I can't even tell
which was really Hyeokchan or you…

09:38.474 --> 09:39.475
The pen.

09:42.103 --> 09:43.104
The engraving.

09:45.315 --> 09:46.316
Who was it?

09:46.816 --> 09:48.484
Was it you or Hyeokchan?

09:53.323 --> 09:55.325
I'm sorry.

09:57.410 --> 09:58.411
If that's fake…

09:59.787 --> 10:01.664
Even if this pen is fake…

10:02.540 --> 10:05.084
Then what was I holding onto
the past seven years?

10:06.211 --> 10:08.921
I even hurt my grandma
because of all that.

10:08.922 --> 10:09.923
Why…

10:11.716 --> 10:13.635
You should've at least told me

10:14.677 --> 10:16.970
when you gave me this pen.

10:16.971 --> 10:21.516
When I believed you like a fool,
you should've told me the truth.

10:21.517 --> 10:22.727
I needed time.

10:23.603 --> 10:24.687
My memories aren't…

10:29.400 --> 10:30.401
I'm sorry.

10:31.569 --> 10:32.653
It's all my fault.

10:32.654 --> 10:35.405
Do you even know what it meant
for me to hold your hand?

10:35.406 --> 10:37.532
To open my heart to you?

10:37.533 --> 10:39.701
How could you, of all people…

10:39.702 --> 10:41.746
How could you, Seonu Chan?

10:44.874 --> 10:47.794
I'm really sorry I hurt you
by making you find out like this.

10:49.212 --> 10:51.380
I won't ask you
to believe everything I say,

10:51.381 --> 10:52.547
so please…

10:52.548 --> 10:56.386
I was surprised that there was someone
who believed in me this much.

10:57.637 --> 10:58.638
I was grateful.

11:00.014 --> 11:01.933
But you knew me all along.

11:02.976 --> 11:04.477
You knew what hurt me the most

11:04.978 --> 11:06.980
and what would break me the easiest.

11:08.314 --> 11:09.399
I thought…

11:13.027 --> 11:14.696
you were like a miracle to me.

11:16.864 --> 11:18.408
But to you…

11:20.368 --> 11:22.203
I was just an experiment.

11:27.041 --> 11:28.251
It's not…

11:30.086 --> 11:31.212
No…

11:34.799 --> 11:36.341
Haran, that's not true.

11:36.342 --> 11:37.593
Never.

11:38.094 --> 11:40.722
If you were fake,
you shouldn't have made me like you.

11:41.306 --> 11:43.683
You shouldn't have made me
trust you this much!

11:46.978 --> 11:48.979
I didn't even know it was all fake,

11:48.980 --> 11:50.814
and I foolishly laughed, cried,

11:50.815 --> 11:53.525
and was happy because of you.

11:56.112 --> 11:59.449
It must have been so fun watching me.

12:00.283 --> 12:01.659
Like a spring picnic.

12:13.838 --> 12:15.214
Wait.

12:16.591 --> 12:17.841
Please.

12:17.842 --> 12:21.178
Please, let me explain.

12:21.179 --> 12:22.180
Explain what?

12:23.264 --> 12:25.391
That you were still sincere?
That's so obvious.

12:26.768 --> 12:29.811
No matter what you say about it,
the truth won't change.

12:29.812 --> 12:31.606
Everything was fake from the start,

12:32.440 --> 12:34.650
and every moment you spent with me,

12:35.443 --> 12:37.362
you were hiding that secret from me.

12:40.323 --> 12:41.741
I knew it was too good to be true.

12:42.241 --> 12:44.535
There's no way
someone like me could be that happy.

12:45.203 --> 12:48.997
Whenever I feel like I'm really happy,

12:48.998 --> 12:50.083
I lose someone.

12:51.959 --> 12:53.043
Hi!

12:53.044 --> 12:54.921
-  Hi.
-  They look so excited.

12:56.547 --> 12:58.006
Dad!

12:58.007 --> 12:59.341
Mom and Dad, 13 years ago…

13:00.802 --> 13:02.135
Just five minutes left.

13:05.431 --> 13:06.724
Hyeokchan, seven years ago…

13:07.392 --> 13:08.518
And today.

13:09.143 --> 13:10.937
You, Seonu Chan.

13:14.273 --> 13:16.484
This is the kind of ending that suits me.

13:17.110 --> 13:19.112
I'm not allowed to be happy.

13:20.530 --> 13:22.532
You've proven that once again.

13:25.410 --> 13:26.411
Haran, please.

13:27.161 --> 13:28.538
If we end things like this,

13:29.122 --> 13:32.542
you'll go back
to putting up walls around you.

13:33.334 --> 13:35.461
- If you do that because of me--
- You're right.

13:36.504 --> 13:38.756
You just pushed me back into winter again.

13:39.632 --> 13:41.676
My past seven years, the present,

13:42.635 --> 13:44.052
and the future.

13:45.138 --> 13:46.806
You've ruined it all for me.

13:50.434 --> 13:52.270
Just let me go.

13:53.604 --> 13:54.730
You disgust me.

15:00.630 --> 15:02.714
Is it still valid?

15:02.715 --> 15:04.674
Being friends. The three-month trial.

15:04.675 --> 15:07.344
Then let's do this.
It'll be like we're on a spring picnic.

15:07.345 --> 15:08.428
Let's have fun.

15:08.429 --> 15:09.931
Ms. Song!

15:18.397 --> 15:20.775
You're Designer Song Haran, right?

15:26.530 --> 15:28.531
I'll wear this every day.

15:33.204 --> 15:34.956
I feel like I'm in a dream.

15:57.979 --> 15:59.980
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

16:10.574 --> 16:11.575
SEONU CHAN

16:59.749 --> 17:01.876
I'm not allowed to be happy.

17:03.002 --> 17:04.754
You've proven that once again.

17:05.546 --> 17:07.839
You just pushed me back into winter again.

17:07.840 --> 17:10.717
My past seven years, the present,

17:10.718 --> 17:12.010
and the future.

17:12.011 --> 17:13.846
You've ruined it all for me.

17:15.056 --> 17:16.599
It's my fault…

17:20.102 --> 17:21.979
I have to do something.

17:26.484 --> 17:29.277
Talk it out with Haran.

17:29.278 --> 17:33.907
If you're sincere,
I'm sure she'll understand.

18:00.142 --> 18:01.644
Haran?

18:03.104 --> 18:04.729
What's going on?

18:04.730 --> 18:06.607
Why are you cooped up in here again?

18:07.191 --> 18:09.026
How is this scarf? Should I wear it?

18:10.361 --> 18:12.780
I'm heading to work in 10 minutes.
Do you want to…

18:15.950 --> 18:16.951
What?

18:17.910 --> 18:19.203
You're sweating.

18:21.038 --> 18:23.249
Haran, you're burning up.

18:24.250 --> 18:26.376
I told you to dress warmly, didn't I?

18:26.377 --> 18:28.962
- Let's go to the hospital.
- I can just take medicine.

18:28.963 --> 18:30.798
Medicine won't be enough right now.

18:31.549 --> 18:33.216
You should just rest today…

18:33.217 --> 18:35.678
How can I when Grandma's away?

18:36.262 --> 18:38.555
I'll get dressed, so get the car ready.

18:46.439 --> 18:48.190
Oh… Let's talk.

18:48.816 --> 18:51.526
I know you don't want to see me…

18:51.527 --> 18:53.570
but just hear me out.

18:53.571 --> 18:57.158
If we end things like this,
you'll go back to how you used to be.

19:00.494 --> 19:01.495
All right.

19:02.329 --> 19:04.706
You don't have to look at me
or listen to me.

19:04.707 --> 19:07.209
So please, just look at this.

19:11.297 --> 19:14.007
How many pills should you take?

19:14.008 --> 19:16.886
- Oh? It's Chan.
- Don't open the window. Just go.

19:17.386 --> 19:19.305
- But it's Chan.
- Just go.

19:20.014 --> 19:21.056
Okay.

19:25.770 --> 19:28.439
If he came all the way here,
it must be pretty important.

19:29.231 --> 19:31.150
What's going on? Did you have a fight?

19:32.109 --> 19:33.486
Let's just go quietly.

19:34.487 --> 19:37.281
He looks so down, though.

19:43.954 --> 19:46.039
Let's continue after lunch.

19:46.040 --> 19:48.416
All right.

19:48.417 --> 19:50.084
Can you--

19:50.085 --> 19:51.419
It's Chan.

19:51.420 --> 19:52.463
Hey, Chan.

20:00.513 --> 20:01.638
Ms. Song.

20:01.639 --> 20:03.306
I don't have any meetings today.

20:03.307 --> 20:04.683
Don't let anyone in.

20:05.309 --> 20:07.269
Huh? But Chan…

20:07.770 --> 20:09.687
I won't make any excuses.

20:09.688 --> 20:12.649
I know you don't want to listen,
so please…

20:12.650 --> 20:14.860
No exceptions.
Don't let anyone in my office.

20:27.540 --> 20:31.001
I'll buy lunch today.

20:31.585 --> 20:33.212
Why don't you join us since you're here?

20:33.838 --> 20:35.714
No, I'm okay.

20:39.009 --> 20:40.010
Ah.

20:40.511 --> 20:43.263
Please give this to her.
Don't tell her it's from me.

20:43.264 --> 20:44.473
Okay.

20:45.391 --> 20:47.226
He looks more sick than her, though.

21:10.416 --> 21:12.209
Does this one stand out too much?

21:14.003 --> 21:16.170
It'll feel more like noise
than a focal point.

21:16.171 --> 21:17.423
What do you think?

21:18.048 --> 21:19.215
I agree.

21:19.216 --> 21:21.134
Then let's stick to the flow instead.

21:21.135 --> 21:22.428
- All right.
- Good.

21:23.637 --> 21:28.057
Oh. But has anyone
seen our robot, Mr. Yeon?

21:28.058 --> 21:31.436
I have to ask him
about our press cut deadline.

21:31.437 --> 21:35.273
I haven't seen
his perfectly groomed hair for days.

21:35.274 --> 21:38.276
He must be incredibly busy
taking care of things for Ms. Kim.

21:38.277 --> 21:42.031
Right. He'll be busy
making up for her absence.

21:42.531 --> 21:45.576
But when did Mr. Yeon
start working in Nana Atelier?

21:46.410 --> 21:47.411
Since he was 19.

21:49.121 --> 21:51.205
- Nineteen?
-  Legend.

21:53.000 --> 21:56.419
But no matter how busy he is,
he does seem to have disappeared.

21:56.420 --> 21:58.547
-  Mmm.
- Right.

21:59.048 --> 22:00.214
It's like he just quit.

22:00.215 --> 22:02.217
What if he really did?

22:07.556 --> 22:10.476
He could have,
if he's been working since he was 19.

22:14.355 --> 22:17.148
I organized the color differences
and confirmed the pigment.

22:17.149 --> 22:19.442
I also picked the other SS looks.

22:19.443 --> 22:21.654
And you need to approve this.

22:26.617 --> 22:28.118
How are you feeling?

22:31.080 --> 22:33.498
- I should ask the same thing.
- What?

22:33.499 --> 22:35.541
You look really unwell.

22:35.542 --> 22:38.796
- Oh… I just have a light cold.
- That's not all, is it?

22:40.047 --> 22:41.130
What is it?

22:41.131 --> 22:45.344
Has Mr. Seonu gotten worse?

22:46.345 --> 22:49.013
No, nothing's wrong.

22:49.014 --> 22:52.767
Just focus on your condition
before your surgery.

22:52.768 --> 22:54.812
Don't worry about me or the company.

22:55.646 --> 22:58.356
Mr. Park, you can head home today.
I'll stay here.

22:58.357 --> 22:59.358
Mmm-mmm.

22:59.942 --> 23:02.777
I told you I'm in charge here.

23:02.778 --> 23:06.739
You should hurry home and rest.

23:06.740 --> 23:09.158
You might end up
getting hospitalized instead of me.

23:09.159 --> 23:10.868
You look like you'll collapse.

23:10.869 --> 23:12.162
Go home.

23:12.621 --> 23:14.581
Then please take care of her.

23:15.457 --> 23:16.875
Thank you, Mr. Park.

23:17.626 --> 23:18.710
My pleasure.

23:20.129 --> 23:22.089
-  Bye, then.
- Bye.

23:25.509 --> 23:27.136
It seems like something's up.

23:29.930 --> 23:31.974
Ms. Kim Nabong, worry about yourself

23:32.516 --> 23:35.226
until your surgery.

23:35.227 --> 23:36.228
Hmm?

23:42.484 --> 23:43.609
Is this okay?

23:43.610 --> 23:44.777
Yes, it's okay.

23:44.778 --> 23:46.780
- Tell me if it hurts.
- Okay.

23:47.948 --> 23:50.033
You're checking with him again.

23:50.034 --> 23:52.201
Of course. I should record this every day.

23:52.202 --> 23:54.996
He has to pass
the medical test in February.

23:54.997 --> 23:56.914
Then let's check your ankle now.

23:56.915 --> 23:59.334
Try pulling with strength.

24:01.920 --> 24:03.171
It doesn't hurt?

24:03.172 --> 24:04.839
No, not at all.

24:04.840 --> 24:08.468
Your range of motion
has improved a lot since last week.

24:08.469 --> 24:09.635
Right, Doctor?

24:09.636 --> 24:11.262
Yes.

24:11.263 --> 24:13.598
Then, next week,
we'll fit you with an ankle brace

24:13.599 --> 24:14.891
and work on standing up.

24:14.892 --> 24:17.101
Don't strain yourself. Good job.

24:17.102 --> 24:18.479
- Thank you.
- Bye.

24:19.480 --> 24:21.814
That was two degrees more than last week.

24:21.815 --> 24:23.691
Are you sure it didn't hurt?

24:23.692 --> 24:25.902
I know my body better than anyone.

24:25.903 --> 24:29.530
I feel like I'll be able to get up soon
and start throwing balls.

24:31.116 --> 24:34.368
Mr. Cha, you really have
exceptional recovery speed,

24:34.369 --> 24:35.870
as expected.

24:35.871 --> 24:38.915
Then let's start
outdoors practice tomorrow

24:38.916 --> 24:41.085
so you don't lose your touch.

24:41.877 --> 24:44.462
Yes, Coach. Let's do this.

24:45.547 --> 24:47.049
Ah.

24:48.967 --> 24:50.343
- Hang on.
- Sure.

24:50.344 --> 24:51.595
Hello?

25:07.111 --> 25:08.153
Come in.

25:11.156 --> 25:12.741
Are you just going to leave again?

25:13.283 --> 25:14.576
Come in.

25:17.704 --> 25:18.789
Mr. Yeon.

25:43.021 --> 25:44.189
I've failed you again.

25:46.650 --> 25:49.278
I've never protected you properly.

25:53.657 --> 25:54.782
I'm sorry.

25:54.783 --> 25:55.993
So,

25:58.162 --> 26:00.664
were you going to wait until I recovered

26:01.665 --> 26:02.875
and try to quit again?

26:03.667 --> 26:05.376
Like that day, 13 years ago?

26:10.799 --> 26:13.135
Good job. You can go now.

26:14.261 --> 26:15.845
Ms. Kim…

26:15.846 --> 26:18.347
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

26:18.348 --> 26:19.641
I'm sorry, Ms. Kim.

26:20.309 --> 26:22.060
If only I hadn't been sick that day…

26:23.145 --> 26:24.646
If I'd been the one driving…

26:26.815 --> 26:28.775
I couldn't even repay you
for your kindness.

26:29.234 --> 26:30.277
I'm sorry.

26:32.070 --> 26:34.615
If you have time to talk such nonsense,

26:35.157 --> 26:36.158
use that time

26:37.826 --> 26:39.077
to prepare for college.

26:40.871 --> 26:42.706
You'd better get accepted in one try.

26:46.335 --> 26:48.629
You made that same face

26:49.254 --> 26:51.298
after Hyewon and Junho's funeral.

26:56.094 --> 26:58.055
When I met you for the first time,

26:59.598 --> 27:02.059
do you know why I told you to come see me?

27:03.727 --> 27:05.187
You reminded me of my past.

27:06.647 --> 27:08.357
Even if no one noticed,

27:09.775 --> 27:11.401
I did my best

27:12.653 --> 27:15.989
and worked so hard on my own
in Paris when I was 20.

27:21.078 --> 27:22.662
As soon as I turned 20,

27:22.663 --> 27:25.164
I flew to Paris alone
with no friends or family.

27:25.165 --> 27:28.460
I threw myself
into both studying and love.

27:29.586 --> 27:31.296
But I suddenly got pregnant

27:31.880 --> 27:33.715
and gave birth by myself.

27:34.216 --> 27:35.676
I struggled so hard

27:36.677 --> 27:39.388
attending fashion school,
carrying a baby on my back.

27:43.767 --> 27:48.105
I told myself that someone
would notice my efforts someday,

27:49.523 --> 27:50.941
and I pushed through.

27:52.985 --> 27:54.319
Once I succeeded,

27:56.029 --> 27:57.114
I felt so much pity

27:58.699 --> 28:00.075
and pride

28:00.784 --> 28:02.369
for myself back then.

28:06.373 --> 28:07.708
I saw you that day,

28:08.834 --> 28:11.503
and I felt the same way about you.

28:12.838 --> 28:14.505
That's why I reached out a hand.

28:14.506 --> 28:17.926
Because I wanted to acknowledge
your efforts.

28:18.719 --> 28:19.720
You…

28:21.138 --> 28:22.472
took care of me…

28:25.434 --> 28:27.393
and changed my life, but…

28:27.394 --> 28:29.312
I never thought of it like that,

28:30.689 --> 28:32.857
but you've already repaid me enough.

28:32.858 --> 28:34.191
Without you,

28:34.192 --> 28:37.029
neither I nor my company nor my family

28:37.821 --> 28:40.072
would have gotten this far.

28:40.073 --> 28:41.158
No.

28:42.075 --> 28:43.076
I…

28:44.661 --> 28:46.495
I don't have the right to stay…

28:46.496 --> 28:47.873
Taeseok.

28:53.587 --> 28:54.880
Put down that burden now.

28:58.467 --> 29:00.469
You couldn't have prevented the accident

29:01.386 --> 29:02.721
by driving that day,

29:03.889 --> 29:05.599
nor could you have prevented this

29:06.516 --> 29:07.934
by noticing more quickly.

29:08.727 --> 29:11.687
No one in my family
blames you for what happened.

29:11.688 --> 29:14.649
You've been holding onto that guilt
because you're too kind.

29:16.109 --> 29:17.735
But you don't have to do that.

29:17.736 --> 29:19.905
Put it all down now.

29:25.952 --> 29:27.370
You've done a great job so far

29:28.371 --> 29:30.082
working by my side.

29:31.792 --> 29:35.002
So stay with me.

29:54.940 --> 29:55.941
Mr. Yeon.

29:57.359 --> 29:58.692
I'm sorry.

29:58.693 --> 30:00.069
I'm really sorry.

30:00.070 --> 30:01.487
I'm sorry.

30:01.488 --> 30:02.948
I'm really sorry.

30:04.324 --> 30:05.325
I…

30:06.409 --> 30:08.078
shouldn't be sick.

30:29.683 --> 30:32.310
Do you want one?

30:45.240 --> 30:46.575
I'm sorry.

30:47.576 --> 30:49.410
I didn't mean to eavesdrop,

30:49.411 --> 30:53.790
but I brought fruits for Grandma
and ended up overhearing.

30:56.209 --> 31:00.087
Ah. So that's why
you were at Mom and Dad's grave.

31:00.088 --> 31:01.673
Okay. I understand now.

31:02.716 --> 31:05.384
- I'm sorry.
- Stop saying you're sorry.

31:05.385 --> 31:09.388
Like Grandma said,
none of us have ever blamed you.

31:09.389 --> 31:10.848
Not for a single second.

31:10.849 --> 31:13.310
Mom, Dad. It's not his fault, right?

31:15.854 --> 31:18.064
You heard that, right? They said no.

31:24.154 --> 31:25.237
Here.

31:25.238 --> 31:29.618
Have this sweet and sour candy
that you love so much…

31:34.456 --> 31:35.999
and leave all your burdens behind.

31:39.711 --> 31:40.712
Have this

31:41.755 --> 31:43.006
and cheer up.

31:46.635 --> 31:48.553
- You're giving this to me again.
- What?

31:49.095 --> 31:51.306
Didn't you give me one last time?

31:52.599 --> 31:53.683
Did I?

31:57.479 --> 32:00.273
It's so sour. Why is it so sour?

32:07.697 --> 32:10.283
YOU SAVED ME TOO

32:16.456 --> 32:18.959
No exceptions.
Don't let anyone in my office.

32:33.431 --> 32:35.141
MR. PARK

32:39.229 --> 32:40.230
Yes, Mr. Park.

32:40.897 --> 32:42.356
What's wrong with your voice?

32:42.357 --> 32:43.649
Did you catch a cold?

32:43.650 --> 32:44.651
Oh…

32:46.569 --> 32:49.321
Maybe it's because you're not here.

32:49.322 --> 32:50.615
I have no one to talk to,

32:51.825 --> 32:55.036
so I guess my voice is a bit rusty.

32:55.620 --> 32:58.039
Is…

32:59.124 --> 33:00.583
something the matter?

33:01.209 --> 33:03.712
Besides the fact that I miss you,
everything's fine.

33:04.504 --> 33:06.256
It must be tough at the hospital.

33:07.716 --> 33:10.343
I'm doing well here with Genius,

33:11.720 --> 33:12.762
so don't worry

33:13.763 --> 33:15.181
and take care of yourself, too.

33:15.849 --> 33:16.933
All right.

33:28.194 --> 33:29.404
I'm okay.

33:30.697 --> 33:33.783
No, I'll make sure everything's okay.

33:36.953 --> 33:38.955
Everything will be okay.

33:46.880 --> 33:48.214
Song Haran.

33:50.633 --> 33:52.052
You saved me,

33:52.802 --> 33:54.095
seven years ago.

33:54.763 --> 33:56.306
You saved me back then!

34:05.899 --> 34:06.900
I'm sorry.

34:07.609 --> 34:09.526
Seven years ago and now,

34:09.527 --> 34:11.863
I've wanted to show you the real me.

34:13.531 --> 34:15.992
I should have told you, no matter what.

34:21.247 --> 34:22.374
It's all my fault.

34:27.003 --> 34:29.881
Please, just look at this.
Everything's in here.

34:31.007 --> 34:33.843
Stories that you don't know
about back then.

34:37.931 --> 34:39.265
Let me ask you two things.

34:41.017 --> 34:42.769
Just say yes or no.

34:46.231 --> 34:47.690
If I look at this,

34:49.818 --> 34:51.236
will it change the fact

34:53.405 --> 34:56.074
that you pretended to be Hyeokchan
and messaged me…

34:59.202 --> 35:00.203
seven years ago?

35:05.583 --> 35:07.209
- No.
-  Then,

35:07.210 --> 35:09.671
does it change the fact

35:11.756 --> 35:14.426
that you kept this secret from me
the whole time…

35:17.470 --> 35:18.555
while you were with me?

35:19.597 --> 35:21.766
- Haran.
- Say yes or no.

35:25.061 --> 35:26.062
No.

35:27.772 --> 35:29.774
- But--
- Then it won't change my mind.

35:31.359 --> 35:33.026
If those two facts don't change,

35:33.027 --> 35:35.196
then whatever explanation you give

35:36.364 --> 35:37.449
or whatever you do,

35:38.199 --> 35:39.576
it won't change my mind.

35:42.203 --> 35:46.291
If you still think the lies you told
can be explained by something,

35:47.917 --> 35:49.836
then you still have no clue

35:52.130 --> 35:54.007
how you've shattered my heart

35:55.842 --> 35:59.637
and how you've destroyed
the past seven years of my life.

36:02.098 --> 36:03.933
Don't ever show up in front of me again.

36:05.685 --> 36:06.895
When I see you,

36:08.438 --> 36:12.358
I feel like I'm going to lose my mind
thinking about the seven years I lost.

36:16.404 --> 36:18.322
I won't even
think about staying with you.

36:18.323 --> 36:21.284
But you'll go back
to how you were seven years ago…

37:22.011 --> 37:24.888
Cha Yougyum!

37:24.889 --> 37:26.849
Your pitching is still amazing.

37:26.850 --> 37:31.603
No wonder you were always named MVP
at every tournament.

37:38.820 --> 37:40.655
Oh, gosh, I missed it.

37:46.077 --> 37:47.494
Hadam, let's stop.

37:47.495 --> 37:48.787
You must be tired.

37:48.788 --> 37:50.914
I'll ask Changmo to help me later.

37:50.915 --> 37:52.875
No. We can do it.

37:52.876 --> 37:54.168
Let's go.

37:55.753 --> 37:57.422
All right, throw it.

38:04.512 --> 38:07.473
Gosh, I missed it again. I'll go get it.

38:23.239 --> 38:24.449
Did we overdo it?

38:25.199 --> 38:26.200
You must be tired.

38:26.951 --> 38:28.076
Not at all.

38:28.077 --> 38:29.661
I know my body best.

38:29.662 --> 38:31.706
I feel much lighter now.

38:33.458 --> 38:34.459
Oh, right.

38:35.710 --> 38:39.463
My team's visiting later,
so it's going to be really noisy.

38:39.464 --> 38:40.756
You should head home now.

38:40.757 --> 38:43.468
Then I should go and study rehabilitation.

38:44.510 --> 38:46.762
Have fun with the guys.
I'll call you later.

38:46.763 --> 38:47.847
Okay.

38:52.185 --> 38:53.685
Those punks.

38:53.686 --> 38:56.397
I should give them some snacks.

38:57.231 --> 38:59.525
Hmm? It's pretty quiet, though.

39:08.743 --> 39:10.160
Out!

39:11.579 --> 39:13.331
FINAL, CHEONGSOL HIGH 3
HANEUL HIGH 2

39:23.967 --> 39:25.426
Yougyum.

39:27.804 --> 39:28.805
Hadam…

39:30.431 --> 39:31.557
What do I do?

39:37.563 --> 39:38.564
I…

39:39.107 --> 39:40.900
I don't think I can make it.

39:42.944 --> 39:45.947
I know my body better than anyone.

40:02.755 --> 40:05.425
CHEONGSOL HIGH SCHOOL WINS

40:17.562 --> 40:18.646
What is it?

40:19.647 --> 40:20.648
Can't you sleep?

40:21.107 --> 40:22.566
Should I turn the light off?

40:22.567 --> 40:23.650
No.

40:23.651 --> 40:24.652
Manjae,

40:25.486 --> 40:26.612
you should go home.

40:27.447 --> 40:28.823
Go and sleep comfortably.

40:30.533 --> 40:32.201
I'll go once you're asleep.

40:32.744 --> 40:34.245
But why can't you sleep?

40:37.373 --> 40:38.374
I just…

40:39.751 --> 40:41.586
have a lot on my mind.

40:42.462 --> 40:43.463
Goodness.

40:43.963 --> 40:45.173
It's snowing.

40:46.549 --> 40:48.468
Oh. It is.

40:55.099 --> 40:57.852
Why do you have a lot on your mind?

40:58.686 --> 41:02.940
You know I've been tough
since I was little, right?

41:04.275 --> 41:05.276
But…

41:06.694 --> 41:09.739
thinking about going under anesthesia
and getting surgery

41:11.574 --> 41:12.867
makes me feel a bit nervous.

41:18.206 --> 41:21.042
I'm sure the surgery will go well.

41:21.876 --> 41:25.004
Just be yourself, the strong Kim Nana,

41:26.130 --> 41:27.256
and get through this.

41:28.007 --> 41:32.178
I'm more worried about something else
than drilling a hole in my skull.

41:32.929 --> 41:33.930
What is it?

41:35.306 --> 41:37.058
I have to shave my head here.

41:37.892 --> 41:40.103
That would ruin my look.

41:40.603 --> 41:42.188
Why does that worry me more?

41:44.690 --> 41:47.400
You really are the Chuncheon fashionista.

41:50.655 --> 41:51.656
This won't do.

41:52.365 --> 41:55.493
I should protect your look.

41:56.369 --> 41:57.702
Hang on.

41:57.703 --> 41:58.830
What?

42:01.541 --> 42:02.542
Oh, my.

42:03.668 --> 42:05.545
This is hand-knitted.

42:06.587 --> 42:07.964
Did you really…

42:13.511 --> 42:17.265
I knitted it in secret
while you were sleeping.

42:18.933 --> 42:22.311
But I think I'm a knitting genius.

42:23.396 --> 42:25.814
I followed along easily.

42:25.815 --> 42:27.191
I might have to open

42:27.817 --> 42:30.652
a knitting workshop in my coffee shop.

42:30.653 --> 42:31.903
Huh?

42:31.904 --> 42:33.363
How did you…

42:33.364 --> 42:36.325
Would you like to try it on?

42:41.831 --> 42:42.832
Wow.

42:45.042 --> 42:46.334
You look beautiful.

42:46.335 --> 42:47.544
- Really?
- Yes.

42:47.545 --> 42:48.671
- Let me see.
- Okay.

42:50.882 --> 42:52.049
Here, look.

42:57.597 --> 42:59.182
Nabong.

42:59.932 --> 43:01.684
After the surgery,

43:04.187 --> 43:05.354
why don't you rest

43:06.564 --> 43:07.565
by my side?

43:08.941 --> 43:10.025
What?

43:10.026 --> 43:11.319
Kim Nabong.

43:12.445 --> 43:15.114
It took a long time,

43:16.240 --> 43:17.742
but will you begin

43:18.409 --> 43:20.870
your second "La Vie en Rose"

43:21.704 --> 43:23.748
with me, Park Manjae?

43:31.297 --> 43:32.506
Hmm?

43:33.549 --> 43:34.550
Manjae.

43:58.199 --> 44:00.868
You've been through so much all this time.

44:02.745 --> 44:04.121
So get some rest

44:05.581 --> 44:06.582
by my side now.

44:21.013 --> 44:22.139
Hey, roomie.

44:23.099 --> 44:25.017
Why are you sitting there in the dark?

44:32.275 --> 44:33.276
Hey.

44:33.943 --> 44:35.111
Is something wrong?

44:37.113 --> 44:38.155
She…

44:39.448 --> 44:40.992
found out about everything.

44:41.826 --> 44:43.661
I didn't have the chance to explain.

44:49.875 --> 44:51.502
It's all my fault,

44:52.545 --> 44:56.007
but she's the one suffering
when she did nothing wrong.

44:57.174 --> 44:59.051
It hurts so much

45:02.179 --> 45:03.764
to see her in pain…

45:05.558 --> 45:08.102
But I must be crazy.

45:10.104 --> 45:11.522
Despite everything,

45:15.026 --> 45:16.027
I still

45:17.737 --> 45:19.613
want to see her so badly.

45:24.493 --> 45:26.329
If I lose her like this,

45:28.706 --> 45:29.999
if I…

45:32.001 --> 45:33.961
make her return to her old self,

45:35.212 --> 45:36.213
then…

45:37.340 --> 45:38.924
Then…

45:40.634 --> 45:42.178
Oh, dear…

45:43.721 --> 45:47.599
I did wonder if something was wrong. Gosh.

45:51.062 --> 45:52.145
You're burning up.

45:52.146 --> 45:53.689
How long have you been like this?

45:54.190 --> 45:56.274
Huh? Oh?

45:56.275 --> 45:58.985
Hey! Roomie!

45:58.986 --> 46:00.111
Hey!

46:00.112 --> 46:01.197
Chan!

46:04.367 --> 46:05.785
Goodness.

46:12.375 --> 46:15.961
I want to stay by her side

46:16.796 --> 46:19.214
in spring, in summer,

46:19.215 --> 46:20.841
in fall, and in winter.

46:21.592 --> 46:22.675
I want

46:22.676 --> 46:25.136
to stay by her side,

46:25.137 --> 46:27.097
but I don't know what to do.

46:28.474 --> 46:31.394
Do you need someone to talk to?

46:32.353 --> 46:33.770
Ah…

46:33.771 --> 46:35.439
I made some assumptions,

46:36.107 --> 46:39.276
but there was a lot more I didn't know.

46:40.611 --> 46:43.406
You must have had
such a hard time until now.

46:44.240 --> 46:45.658
You've been through a lot.

46:46.659 --> 46:49.453
I want to tell her everything
and stay by her side,

46:50.162 --> 46:51.956
but if I tell her about myself,

46:54.375 --> 46:55.626
it will hurt her.

46:56.836 --> 46:58.795
I'm not even sure

46:58.796 --> 47:01.382
if I can explain myself to her
without reopening

47:03.634 --> 47:04.760
her old wounds.

47:05.594 --> 47:07.388
But if you're this sincere,

47:07.972 --> 47:10.975
don't you think
she'll realize it in the end?

47:11.934 --> 47:14.395
To be honest, I'm scared.

47:15.729 --> 47:17.730
If I act rashly,

47:17.731 --> 47:20.776
my flawed memories might ruin everything.

47:21.360 --> 47:22.361
I'm scared…

47:25.781 --> 47:27.324
I'll hurt her again.

47:27.867 --> 47:28.909
Chan.

47:30.202 --> 47:31.912
After living all these years,

47:32.371 --> 47:35.331
what I've learned is that
waiting until everything's perfect

47:35.332 --> 47:37.126
isn't always the answer.

47:37.877 --> 47:40.296
For people and for love.

47:41.130 --> 47:42.381
"Memento Mori."

47:42.882 --> 47:44.425
You said
you don't want regrets.

47:45.009 --> 47:46.217
If you keep waiting,

47:46.218 --> 47:48.386
you might lose your chance
and regret it later.

47:48.387 --> 47:51.724
Why don't you show her
how sincere you are first?

47:52.641 --> 47:55.686
It won't be too late
to take care of other things later.

48:04.278 --> 48:08.032
I should get ready
to explain myself to her.

48:10.451 --> 48:11.660
I should start

48:12.244 --> 48:14.163
by what happened seven years ago

48:16.874 --> 48:18.459
and tell her in my own way.

48:23.797 --> 48:25.632
It's so cold.

48:25.633 --> 48:28.801
Why are you brooding out here in the cold?

48:28.802 --> 48:30.345
What time is it?

48:30.346 --> 48:31.763
It's past midnight.

48:31.764 --> 48:34.140
How long have you been here?
You're already unwell.

48:34.141 --> 48:35.142
Come inside.

48:36.101 --> 48:38.312
Oh, uh… Did you go to the hospital?

48:40.314 --> 48:42.274
Haran, what is it?

48:43.025 --> 48:44.944
Huh? Is something wrong?

48:45.611 --> 48:46.904
What's going on?

48:47.488 --> 48:49.240
- Hayeong.
- Yes?

48:50.741 --> 48:52.076
I want to wake up.

48:54.828 --> 48:57.373
I thought I was in a dream until now,

48:58.749 --> 49:00.334
but I guess it was a nightmare.

49:03.128 --> 49:05.005
I want to wake up,

49:06.215 --> 49:07.925
but I don't know how.

49:09.885 --> 49:13.389
- Haran.
- We're not meant to be together.

49:15.724 --> 49:19.103
I have to forget things
that seem impossible to forget.

49:22.189 --> 49:23.566
But I don't know

49:25.192 --> 49:27.278
how to get over everything.

49:51.802 --> 49:54.388
Her fever dropped.

49:56.807 --> 49:58.309
Gosh…

50:07.192 --> 50:08.235
What?

50:09.778 --> 50:11.904
Gosh. What time is it?

50:11.905 --> 50:14.033
0202
NOV 29 SAT

50:14.742 --> 50:15.868
Are you here?

50:16.994 --> 50:17.995
What?

50:19.204 --> 50:20.372
Where did she go?

50:21.999 --> 50:23.042
Haran!

50:30.549 --> 50:32.384
HAYEONG

50:34.136 --> 50:35.929
What?

50:37.973 --> 50:39.516
Where did she go?

50:46.940 --> 50:48.192
DESIGNER SONG HAYEONG

51:07.169 --> 51:09.128
Hey, Hayeong.

51:09.129 --> 51:12.007
Chan, sorry to call you so late.

51:12.716 --> 51:14.426
But did Haran contact you?

51:16.178 --> 51:19.055
Why? What's wrong?

51:19.056 --> 51:21.391
Haran's gone.

51:21.392 --> 51:24.352
The car's gone,
but she's not at the office either.

51:24.353 --> 51:28.190
You're the only one
I could ask where she could be.

51:29.316 --> 51:32.151
I feel so anxious after what she said.

51:32.152 --> 51:36.281
She said she was in a dream,
but it was a nightmare.

51:41.203 --> 51:43.413
I think I know where she is.

51:43.414 --> 51:45.456
Where are you going?
You're still burning up.

51:45.457 --> 51:47.292
I have to go find her.

51:48.168 --> 51:49.252
It has to be me.

51:49.253 --> 51:52.172
What are you saying?
Did something happen to Haran?

51:53.257 --> 51:54.842
Huh? Chan!

52:01.140 --> 52:03.100
She said
you're not meant to be together

52:03.809 --> 52:05.518
and that she has to forget it.

52:05.519 --> 52:08.313
I couldn't understand what she was saying,

52:08.897 --> 52:11.066
but she's really sick right now.

52:12.192 --> 52:13.901
I feel like I'm in a dream.

52:13.902 --> 52:16.947
Those words sounded a bit sad.

52:17.489 --> 52:20.617
It sounds like
they're not meant to be together.

52:36.800 --> 52:40.303
I said I won't ever forget

52:40.304 --> 52:42.430
this moment.

52:42.431 --> 52:45.099
Ah, and in spring…

52:45.100 --> 52:47.810
Let's go see
the cherry blossoms in spring.

52:47.811 --> 52:49.938
We'll have shaved ice in summer…

52:50.689 --> 52:52.983
Oh, and go to the beach.

52:53.901 --> 52:55.736
We'll see the autumn leaves in fall,

52:56.236 --> 52:59.114
and in winter,
it would be fun to go snowboarding.

53:18.634 --> 53:20.218
Do you have any idea
what you've done?

53:20.219 --> 53:22.303
-  You must've jumped at the chance.
-  I love you, Chan.

53:22.304 --> 53:23.721
Kang Hyeokchan.

53:23.722 --> 53:25.057
Did you have fun…

54:09.142 --> 54:12.854
HADONGDO-GIL

54:17.192 --> 54:18.277
No…

54:19.528 --> 54:20.529
No…

54:21.029 --> 54:22.405
Please…

54:24.783 --> 54:25.951
It can't be…

54:26.535 --> 54:27.994
No way…

54:27.995 --> 54:28.996
Please…

54:30.414 --> 54:31.999
There is no way I caused it.

54:47.472 --> 54:48.932
But what if I did?

54:50.309 --> 54:51.475
Then she…

55:39.107 --> 55:40.192
I wanted…

55:43.403 --> 55:45.113
to check something for the last time.

55:46.448 --> 55:48.074
Seven years ago…

55:49.618 --> 55:50.869
…on the day of the accident.

55:52.746 --> 55:53.789
Did I…

55:55.874 --> 55:57.209
hit Kang Hyeokchan?

55:58.877 --> 56:02.089
Did I hit him and make him fall down?

56:03.465 --> 56:04.675
Is that why his lip tore

56:05.217 --> 56:06.927
and the waste container fell down?

56:11.264 --> 56:12.349
Is that true?

56:13.225 --> 56:14.226
Yes.

56:16.645 --> 56:18.230
You hit Hyeokchan.

56:21.858 --> 56:24.026
But why?

56:24.027 --> 56:25.111
Don't you remember?

56:25.112 --> 56:29.199
The day he came back from his trip,
you told Hyeokchan everything.

56:35.622 --> 56:36.998
Long time no see.

56:37.582 --> 56:39.334
- Right.
- Hang on.

56:42.713 --> 56:46.507
Sorry about this.
We need to switch laptops back.

56:46.508 --> 56:48.510
Move all your data from my laptop.

56:49.386 --> 56:50.469
Oh…

56:50.470 --> 56:51.471
Well…

56:52.431 --> 56:53.597
I…

56:53.598 --> 56:55.142
I have something to tell you.

56:56.268 --> 56:58.603
You do? What is it?

56:59.187 --> 57:00.439
Uh…

57:03.108 --> 57:05.025
While you were away, I--

57:05.026 --> 57:06.820
Will this take long?

57:08.071 --> 57:09.530
Yes, a bit.

57:09.531 --> 57:11.073
Then let's talk later.

57:11.074 --> 57:12.993
I have to meet my professor right now.

57:13.535 --> 57:15.120
I'll see you, uh…

57:15.954 --> 57:17.456
in the lab later.

57:24.421 --> 57:25.964
Right. What is it?

57:26.548 --> 57:28.132
You needed to tell me something.

57:28.133 --> 57:29.301
Your messenger…

57:30.051 --> 57:31.219
What?

57:32.345 --> 57:34.222
While I was using your laptop,

57:35.098 --> 57:38.226
I kept chatting with your girlfriend.

57:42.898 --> 57:44.106
What?

57:45.859 --> 57:48.569
What are you talking about?
Say that again.

57:48.570 --> 57:50.030
We ended up

57:51.072 --> 57:52.449
chatting after that.

57:53.617 --> 57:56.119
But she thinks it was you.

57:57.829 --> 58:00.665
Hyeokchan,
you left your earphones in my car…

58:01.249 --> 58:02.292
Are you saying

58:02.876 --> 58:05.462
you've been talking to Haran

58:06.338 --> 58:07.589
while I was away?

58:08.048 --> 58:09.049
Pretending to be me?

58:14.137 --> 58:15.764
Sorry. It's all my fault.

58:19.184 --> 58:20.185
Hang on.

58:21.853 --> 58:23.104
Who are you to do that?

58:23.980 --> 58:27.776
Why would you ruin everything like this?

58:28.360 --> 58:31.780
Tell me. What sort of things
have you been saying?

58:32.364 --> 58:33.447
Why?

58:33.448 --> 58:36.075
Did you think it was okay
since I asked you a few times?

58:36.076 --> 58:38.495
You were someone nobody even cared about.

58:39.830 --> 58:43.332
Did you get excited
that someone paid attention to you?

58:45.001 --> 58:47.044
Kang Hyeokchan!

58:47.045 --> 58:50.966
You had your eye
on Hyeokchan's girlfriend, Song Haran.

58:51.925 --> 58:53.260
You told him

58:53.802 --> 58:57.012
that you'd been chatting with her
while he was traveling,

58:57.013 --> 58:58.515
so things got heated.

58:59.224 --> 59:00.891
And you ended up hitting him.

59:03.562 --> 59:06.814
Can you still say
you didn't have feelings for her then?

59:09.484 --> 59:10.527
Then…

59:12.404 --> 59:14.990
that accident…

59:16.116 --> 59:18.409
Was it because of the container that fell?

59:18.410 --> 59:20.412
Yes. So how do you feel?

59:20.996 --> 59:23.456
Does it feel good to know the truth?

59:25.709 --> 59:27.042
I told you,

59:27.043 --> 59:29.462
nothing good would come
from digging up the past.

59:34.175 --> 59:36.845
It was all because of you.

59:37.929 --> 59:39.430
You caused the accident,

59:39.431 --> 59:42.392
and it killed Hyeokchan
and hurt a lot of people.

59:49.232 --> 59:51.400
Don't act like it's some grand love story.

59:51.401 --> 59:54.737
You just tried to steal
Hyeokchan's girlfriend

59:54.738 --> 59:57.281
and caused the accident that killed him.

59:57.282 --> 59:58.782
That's all you are.

01:00:02.412 --> 01:00:04.247
Do you have any idea what you've done?

01:00:04.664 --> 01:00:06.333
I'm sorry. It's all my fault.

01:00:09.920 --> 01:00:13.173
It was all my fault.

01:00:21.640 --> 01:00:24.600
Where in the world did you go?
You even left your phone behind.

01:00:24.601 --> 01:00:26.978
You think I wouldn't worry
if you disappeared like that?

01:00:31.816 --> 01:00:33.025
I was so worried.

01:00:33.026 --> 01:00:35.277
You'd better not do that again.

01:00:35.278 --> 01:00:37.072
I'm sorry for making you worry.

01:00:38.823 --> 01:00:41.034
Ah. What about Chan?

01:00:42.077 --> 01:00:44.119
Don't even mention him to me anymore.

01:00:44.120 --> 01:00:46.998
I mean, didn't you meet him?

01:00:47.624 --> 01:00:51.251
He heard you were gone
and started his car right away.

01:00:51.252 --> 01:00:53.295
- Didn't you see him?
- What do you mean?

01:00:53.296 --> 01:00:57.591
I called him late last night
because I didn't know where you were.

01:00:57.592 --> 01:00:59.551
I thought he might know.

01:00:59.552 --> 01:01:03.056
He said he knew where you could be
and left right away.

01:01:03.640 --> 01:01:05.015
Maybe you missed each other.

01:01:05.016 --> 01:01:07.102
Don't contact him about me anymore.

01:01:07.769 --> 01:01:09.229
He has nothing to do with me.

01:01:13.817 --> 01:01:15.318
His phone's off.

01:01:20.699 --> 01:01:22.574
I couldn't react properly.

01:01:24.577 --> 01:01:26.705
It's hard to tell
where sounds are coming from.

01:01:32.711 --> 01:01:34.462
What is it? Where are you going?

01:01:35.505 --> 01:01:37.047
Where are you going?

01:01:37.048 --> 01:01:39.425
This patient was transferred

01:01:39.426 --> 01:01:42.094
after a lab explosion in Boston
seven years ago.

01:01:42.095 --> 01:01:43.804
He was treated for full-body burns,

01:01:43.805 --> 01:01:46.683
and shrapnel is still lodged deep
in the temporal bone.

01:01:47.267 --> 01:01:50.644
It's a high-risk area, so we are only
monitoring it at the moment.

01:01:50.645 --> 01:01:53.063
He also has unilateral hearing loss.

01:01:53.064 --> 01:01:54.606
Burns? Shrapnel?

01:01:54.607 --> 01:01:57.776
He visited the ER recently
after a brief loss of consciousness

01:01:57.777 --> 01:01:59.278
and minor bleeding.

01:01:59.279 --> 01:02:02.614
The outpatient clinic will check
if it's related to the shrapnel.

01:02:02.615 --> 01:02:04.616
That really is a difficult spot.

01:02:04.617 --> 01:02:05.743
That's right.

01:02:05.744 --> 01:02:08.412
If his bleeding
was caused by the shrapnel,

01:02:08.413 --> 01:02:10.205
it may be accompanied

01:02:10.206 --> 01:02:13.208
by neurological symptoms
such as auditory or visual hallucinations.

01:02:13.209 --> 01:02:15.502
There have even been reports
of memory distortion

01:02:15.503 --> 01:02:17.463
in severe cases like this.

01:02:19.674 --> 01:02:22.301
The patient with the shrapnel
in the temporal bone…

01:02:22.302 --> 01:02:23.470
Did he take the exam?

01:02:24.054 --> 01:02:26.473
No, it's past his appointment,
but he hasn't shown up.

01:02:28.016 --> 01:02:29.099
But why do you ask?

01:02:29.100 --> 01:02:30.226
SEONU CHAN

01:02:33.438 --> 01:02:34.564
It's nothing.

01:02:36.149 --> 01:02:37.484
Mr. Park.

01:02:38.068 --> 01:02:39.652
Mr. Park, did you see…

01:03:05.095 --> 01:03:06.386
A three-month trial!

01:03:06.387 --> 01:03:07.930
Just try me out as a free trial.

01:03:07.931 --> 01:03:12.602
As soon as the three months are over,
I'll disappear without a trace.

01:03:19.984 --> 01:03:24.030
END OF TRIAL

01:03:36.376 --> 01:03:38.669
We can proceed
with the model fitting as revised.

01:03:38.670 --> 01:03:40.254
Spring is here!

01:03:40.255 --> 01:03:43.006
Spring is here!

01:03:43.007 --> 01:03:44.551
Look, spring is here.

01:03:45.051 --> 01:03:47.887
The forsythias have started blooming.

01:03:48.346 --> 01:03:50.389
The forsythias are blooming?

01:03:50.390 --> 01:03:52.599
That means we're on a tight schedule.

01:03:52.600 --> 01:03:54.977
All right, let's hang in there
for a few more days.

01:03:54.978 --> 01:03:56.186
- Let's do this!
- Let's do this!

01:03:56.187 --> 01:03:59.022
- Let's do this!
- I'm so sleepy.

01:03:59.023 --> 01:04:00.607
Goodness.

01:04:05.446 --> 01:04:08.992
The seasons of life
don't come in order.

01:04:16.082 --> 01:04:17.542
It really is spring.

01:04:20.587 --> 01:04:22.505
Sometimes, when you think it's spring,

01:04:24.382 --> 01:04:26.301
winter suddenly arrives.

01:04:31.681 --> 01:04:32.682
Take this.

01:04:33.474 --> 01:04:34.475
Oh…

01:04:35.476 --> 01:04:36.935
Then let's do this.

01:04:36.936 --> 01:04:38.730
It'll be like we're on a spring picnic.

01:04:39.606 --> 01:04:40.607
Let's have fun.

01:05:09.677 --> 01:05:12.430
SUMMER, SEVEN YEARS AGO
IT STARTED WITH WALLS

01:05:15.516 --> 01:05:17.518
END OF TRIAL

01:05:19.604 --> 01:05:21.564
The man

01:05:22.232 --> 01:05:24.775
who suddenly lit up
my cold winter last year

01:05:24.776 --> 01:05:26.444
like radiant spring sunlight…

01:05:27.487 --> 01:05:30.323
disappeared from my life.

01:05:55.848 --> 01:05:57.558
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:06:21.666 --> 01:06:23.875
He disappeared.

01:06:23.876 --> 01:06:27.255
The Seonu Chan I know
would never leave like this.

01:06:27.839 --> 01:06:29.214
He disappeared because of me.

01:06:29.215 --> 01:06:31.508
I did something I shouldn't have.

01:06:31.509 --> 01:06:33.593
He's been preparing for a long time.

01:06:33.594 --> 01:06:36.680
It's gotten so bad
that there's nothing they can do.

01:06:36.681 --> 01:06:38.098
Do you remember…

01:06:38.099 --> 01:06:41.852
…how I was trapped in winter for so long?

01:06:41.853 --> 01:06:43.688
I knew you'd understand

01:06:44.981 --> 01:06:46.648
my sincerity.

01:06:46.649 --> 01:06:48.817
Seonu Chan, where are you?

01:06:48.818 --> 01:06:50.987
Where on earth are you?

01:07:03.041 --> 01:07:04.124
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:07:04.125 --> 01:07:05.126
Translated by Juyoung Park
